			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">To my knowledge, the major emulators like FCEUX, Bizhawk (or in the past ZSNES and Nesticle) have never faced a legal challenge from Nintendo/etc. You can interpret that how you will, but I think it shows the likelihood of companies like Nintendo losing that legal battle (despite having profoundly more money). Nintendo has always been hard nosed about these things officially, but they've never put their money where their mouth is. Plus, counter to Nintendo's argument, there is the homebrew market that it can be argued that emulators exist to serve. And again, Nintendo doesn't even own the 6502. Nintendo hasn't even gone after NES/SNES hardware clones.<br /><br />The idea of emulation is not in and of itself illegal. VMWare has an entire industry based on it.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

